Content:
Anonymous functions are very handy, and I think they should really be taken a step further. There's really no reason why it shouldn't be possible to pass an actual function body where a function pointer is required:<p><pre><code>  int v[...];

  qsort( v, ..., (a, b) { return *(int*)a - *(int*)b } );
</code></pre>
Such usage would also have an added benefit of letting the compiler do the type inference for <i>a</i>, <i>b</i> and the return value and not needing to explicitly specify them in qsort() call.
